![high](https://www.gstatic.com/codereviewagent/high-priority.svg)

When the `ARScene` component is unmounted, the webcam stream initiated by AR.js is not stopped, and the injected `<video>` element remains in the DOM. This causes the camera to stay active in the background, draining the device's battery and showing the recording indicator. Stopping all media tracks and removing the video element on unmount resolves this leak.

```
	return () => {
		cancelled = true;
		const video = document.querySelector("body > video");
		if (video) {
			const stream = (video as HTMLVideoElement).srcObject;
			if (stream instanceof MediaStream) {
				stream.getTracks().forEach((track) => track.stop());
			}
			video.remove();
		}
	};
```

![medium](https://www.gstatic.com/codereviewagent/medium-priority.svg)

If the dynamic import of `maplibre-gl` fails (e.g., due to a temporary network issue), the rejected promise is cached in `maplibreLoad` indefinitely. Subsequent attempts to load the map will fail immediately without retrying the network request. Resetting `maplibreLoad` to `null` on rejection allows retrying the import.

```
const loadMapLibre = async (): Promise<MapLibreModule> => {
	if (maplibregl) return maplibregl;
	maplibreLoad ??= Promise.all([
		import("maplibre-gl"),
		import("maplibre-gl/dist/maplibre-gl.css"),
	]).then(([module]) => {
		maplibregl = module;
		return module;
	}).catch((error) => {
		maplibreLoad = null;
		throw error;
	});
	return maplibreLoad;
};
```

